<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note: 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Diapensiaceae" genus="Galax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Galax Linnaeus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">nom. rej.</emphasis>
in favour of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sims. Reveal" authorityName="Sims. Reveal" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Diapensiaceae" genus="Galax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Galax</emphasis>
Sims. Reveal
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 592. 1992) argued that 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Clayton 4</emphasis>
(P-JU), a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Poir.) Brummitt" authorityName="Brummitt" authorityYear="1972" baseAuthorityName="Poir." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Diapensiaceae" genus="Galax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Galax urceolata</emphasis>
(Poir.) Brummitt
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Diapensiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Diapensiaceae</taxonomicName>
), must be the 
<typeStatus pageNumber="529">lectotype</typeStatus>
and therefore proposed the conservation of the name with a conserved type. The Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Taxon</emphasis>
43: 276. 1994) ruled that 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Clayton 4</emphasis>
could not be the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Galax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aphylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">G. aphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it conflicted with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeusâ€™" pageNumber="529">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
generic description (among other things), and that conservation was unnecessary. The Committee ruled that the proposed conserved type was to be treated as a 
<typeStatus pageNumber="529">neotype</typeStatus>
. Reveal (1993) explicitly treated it in this way, and his typification therefore dates from 1993.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
